reviews.text: Very helpful staff and thought provoking artworks. Love popping in here regularly to see what's happening with the local creative arts scene

I love it.
Free entrance.
Small gallery but holds some pieces worth seeing. Free.
Counihan Gallery - Check out the group show starting 22 November  Current Tendencies
Beautiful church, grounds and people
Beautiful place to be
Wasn’t even open during peak posted hours and was tiny anyway

This eclectic outdoor market has remained in the same place with the same standard (local artists & craftspeople selling their own hand-made wares) since the 1970's. There are very few places left in Austin that can claim that lineage. The wide variety of artisans, their work and the price ranges ensure there's something for just about anyone at the 23rd Street Artists Market. I can't think of a place to find a more authentic Austin souvenir than strolling through. My favorite thing about 23rd Street is that it's never the same place twice (great photo ops & eateries all around too). Support your local artists and help Keep Austin Austin.
Nice atmosphere lots of pretty things!
I would also give it less than one star. According to the internet, they should have been there by 8AM. Facebook said 10AM on Sunday. I was there from 9:30-11:30 and no one showed up.
Great local artists! Everything from paintings, jewelry, T-shirts, and other forms of handmade goodies

This is an affordable consistent restaurant. It’s one of the very few eateries in Brunswick that I recommend to friends because it’s authentic and well priced!

Come here for a casual lunch where the food is fresh and light. I particularly like the wraps. There maybe a queue during lunch but it disappears in a zap. People from afar come here because of the bread. It is so tasty!

One of the best places I have ever been to for breakfast. The food was so fresh, authentic, and was utterly delicious. Wide selection of items on the menu, and all items were reasonably priced. The staff were very energetic, cheerful, and friendly. Highly recommended, and a must-visit place in Melbourne. You won’t be disappointed.
Try the cheese pizza or the meat with cheese. Really cheap and tastes amazing. Its a very popular spot so I would recommend it for a late breakfast or evening snack.

Loved this bakery. The atmosphere was vibrant. This place was family friendly and has authentic quality Lebanese food and is reasonably priced. They also sell lots of cooking ingredients as well as imported foods. Great spot and highly recommended.

One of the best Falafel I've ever had. Crisp crust and light spongy from inside... absolutely awesome. The Meat Pizza is flavourful and well baked. The vibe and energy of this place is addictive. A must visit place for a Lebanese food lover.

Had such a fantastic celebratory meal here last night. Highly recommend the banquet, perfect (perhaps a little too much, but since when was that a problem?) amount of food at a very reasonable price. Staff were very accommodating and welcoming. If you are a cocktail fan the Sultan's Negorni is deliciously potent.

Great food, atmosphere and staff. Especially impressed with the staff, very kind, professional and accommodating. Only thing I have a problem with is how small the portion sizes were, I wish they were bigger for the price you pay for them. But food tasted amazing and the mocktails were delicious!

Great new discovery. Had the classic banquet with lots of tasty food. Lamb shoulder was the highlight. Only dish that wasn't to my liking was the school prawns. Too small to taste any flavour of the prawns. Service was very good with waiter explaining the menu and providing recommendations. Will be keen to return to try out other dishes.

Very delicious and well seasoned food! Friendly service. Nice ambience. Just the wait took a while but probably expected at a fine dining restaurant. Salmon skin should be crispy but would definitely come back again. Food was so goood!!!
The food was amazing! My partner was not too impressed reading the menu “ this is not authentic food” but soon changed his mind when we tried the yummy food.

This place is under new management & am so glad I went back to give it a go. Has a newly built bar with multiple cocktails, new cool art work on the walls & delicious authentic food. Loads of Vegetarian & meat options! Staff are very friendly & is now a family run restaurant. Will be back soon - thank you very much for a lovely evening - definitely recommend ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

It's restaurants like these that makes dining out in Melbourne so interesting. They have the classics down pat but surprises with progressive dishes. Check out their cocktails or their good range of beers, which go so well with Indian food. They also have BYO wine which is a plus.
Loved going here! The food was amazing, the prices very reasonable and the staff were very welcoming and friendly. I'm definitely going to come again!

The food was amazing!! The Nan freshly baked with a great balance of garlic butter, the butter chicken was taste and yummy!! Great value for money. The place has also been renovated to a warm, clean touch!!!

ITS    AVRAH 

 NOT KAKE DI HATTI ANY MORE

SO PLEASE.....CORRECT THE NAME 

ENJOY BEST FOOD IN MELBOURNE AT AVRAH

I ordered the Green's Big Breakfast which is very filling and has a good variety on the plate to keep your palate interested. I also ordered the Halloumi and spinach pie (as I always do) because I think it is the best pie out of all the ones they make, and I've tried a few of them. I also ordered the freshly squeezed orange juice and it was fresh although would have been nicer if it were a little more chilled. It was good with everything I ordered, regardless. The place can be relaxed for a nice brunch if you go at the right time, although it can be packed at other times and days.

Amazing food! Plenty of gluten free, vegan, and vegetarian options. And the desserts are to die for! The menu seems very affordable. I had eggs on gluten free toast + avo + hash brown and it came with two eggs and three pieces of toast all for $14. I love the cozy feel inside as well as the beautiful outdoor seats in the back. Will definitely be back for some sweet treats in the future!
Beautiful place. The decor here is totally amazing! You feel like home! The food and coffee here are something so deliciuos! Very quiet and peaceful.

Some people have commented about poor service on their review, clearly these people have become disorientated on their way to McDonald's. Whenever I enter an establishment that serves food and it is crowded with people waiting to get a table I expect the food to be worth the effort.  I was not disappointed. Enjoying an excellent meal in a cosy,intimate   environment like this is something to be cherished and savoured. Thank you to the hard working staff (especially the ones behind the scene) for creating a memorable experience.

I've been frequenting this place for 4+ years, they have a great selection of wholesome food. Excellent coffee, and plenty of pastries and baked goods. Also some awesome vegan, and vegetarian options. Sometimes it gets pretty busy, worthwhile going to their second cafe down the road for more chill vibes :)

A fun place to eat. Buzzing. Lots of different groups enjoying their meals. The kitchen, in full view near the entrance, was jammed with staff going at full speed carving meat for kebabs, plating meals and taking orders. Full halal, so no alcohol. My colleague and I had a great time.
Delicious Lebanese cuisines in a family friendly setting. No alcohol. Polite and prompt service and very accommodating staff. Space for ablution and prayer. Value for money. Recommend it always.

This place is great! Really awsome for a dinner with a few friends or a really big group!

The service is really fast so you can sit down with a grumbling tum and know you'll be fed soon after!  

My favourite pick is the Vegetarian Platter!  It's HUGE--- and for only $20!?! I usually share it with just one friend and we both get a more than substantial feed!  

Ideal to go near the start of the week as it can get louder when it's at a fuller capacity :)

Great food! Cannot fault anything about it! The restaurant is always pretty full so you probably have to wait in line if you don't have a reservation. But the two times I went I was able to find a table. Service is a bit slow, so.maybe because is akqays so full. The atmosphere is not necessary the best but the food is great and that is for me what matters.

Fast service. Great food for a great price. Always bustling with patrons. Would be a good idea to book before coming.  Suitable for small or large groups.  Meals are usually quite generous, so we usually share a couple.
Great centre for University town connecting to community!
My favourite gallery to visit in Melbourne! Always make sure to pay them a visit when I'm in Melbourne.
The best selection of abstract art works in the West. Must go gallery.
The atmosphere was great, nice settings and definitely one of the best in the region.
Always very high quality non-objective and abstract art ! Great art space, friendly and well run!
A great example of the professional standards an independent  run gallery can achieve both through the management and artworks on display well done.

This is my favorite restaurant in Dayton area.  I've been going here for around 20 years.  I would highly recommend one of the meal sized soups, like saté style (#37) and the soft shrimp roll (#2) is amazing. Everyone I've brought for the 1st time always loves these, and the peanut sauce they come with is a mind expanding experience.  The crispy egg noodles (#61) are also a favorite. The fried bananas are a perfect dessert (#184). I have also never been disappointed when trying new dishes of the menu

I don't know where to start when it comes to Little Saigon. Their food is AMAZING! Sincerely, it is so good and flavorful with so many options I know I will never try them all. I maintain they have the best friend spring rolls in the area. They have such delicious Vietnamese dishes with such a huge selection you just have to see their menu to understand. The staff there is so sweet and nice and try so hard to make sure you enjoy your experience. I also think the prices are reasonable, especially with the portions you receive.
Food is great! A good place to get rice when I'm craving for it. Lol. Try their crab rangoon.  It's the best. I also love their fresh spring rolls. 😊

This adorable little Resturaunt was pleasant, and the staff were fun and easy to talk to. Not to mention the food was AMAZING. It was incredible flavorful and there we so many options! Overall, a very VERY good place to eat of your looking to try something new and filling!

This place is a gem! The staff is great, the variety and selection of dishes are extensive and the food itself is amazing. If you enjoy vietnamese food or Asian food in general, this is one of the truly authentic Asian restaurants in the Dayton area. You will not be dissapointed!

Casual spot for a tasty and cheap dinner in Footscray. For veg, the misir wot was unbelievable - amazing flavours from the berbere so highly recommend. If looking for a brew, the beers are at country prices at $5 a pop.

I spent one of the most amazing time  and experienced African cuisine like I had never before. The traditional Ethiopian cuisine was mouthwatering and delicious. The staff were warm welcoming and the service was great. I highly recommend it!

Great authentic food. My first time eating Ethiopian cuisine was at this place and definitely would come back. I've only tried the Key Wat (like a beef stew) which was amazing, full of flavour and will have to come back to try the rest of the menu. Good location as well, close to the station. Really liked the experience of not using cutlery and great if you want to try something different.
Amazing sharing banquets, great service.
We ordered the $16 banquet for 7 and zil zil (beef strips). Everyone was rather well fed, +10 stamina gained. Would reccomend!

The fish was fried to perfection, crispy on the outside and soft and juicy in the inside. The weekend special "duvat"(spelling might not be right) was so tasty and full of flavors. Plenty of food for a very cheap and affordable price. Definitely recommend!!!
Extremely good food at a very reasonable price. Recommendations from the staff are always perfect! Try the ginger tea after a meal¡

Food here is delicious and affordable + service is friendly. Great in a group where you can get the owner to do a platter and get a little bit of everything. They can also do gluten free if someone in the group needs it.
Great atmosphere, terrific service and the food is very tasty. Definitely one of my favourite euthopian restaurants.
Delicious food, great service, excellent value. We will definitely be back!!
Barista Bill is the morning lift to get me thru the day. Excellent coffee & service!
Got a coffee and 1 donut round 12.30pm Tuesday. No jam in donut.  Nozzle blocked.  Later that day, headaches, vomiting,  then 4 days of diarrhea. Left out milk all day or clogged nozzle caused issue?

Good coffee and fresh jam doughnuts. Perfect for an afternoon snack or breakfast if that's how you roll (or should I say, hole). Though I prefer the laid back vibes at the EzyMart next door (see my other review), I can't blame the professionals for choosing this place.
Young man had a smirk on his face while serving me coffee. Nothing like dealing with an unjustified ego before work.

Brilliant coffee, doughnuts and service. Just popped by for something warm after leaving a long shift at work and had one of the best coffee's I've had in ages. I must admit I'm now addicted to their banana bread too!
What a great place! Had the best burgers tonight, beef and with the lot. Chips were delicious and fantastic service. Can't wait to come back again and support this business

Like others have mentioned, service is friendly and personal. Great. The waffle was good.. Initially too dry on the outside I reckon, but then actually worked out well as we took our time eatting it, the ice cream didn't make the waffle soggy. Happy.

Best experience, I went there with 4 other friends on an impulse urge and we were not disappointed!
The man who served us was friendly and relaxed, , the banana split he prepared was outstanding and the ice-cream was really unusual but nice.
Perfect place to kill some time with mates, 5/5 recommend it's a gem of Footscray.
Love this place! Have been here several times and it  never disappoints! Must try the Japanese Tai Parfait! Absolutely love this dessert!

They do a good TBone. Really good for the price. Haven't tried the sweets but will give them a go if I have more time. Try this place, there's nuthin' quite like it in Footscray and they aim to please.
Eye opening, literally. And well presented;full of interesting and somewhat excellent photography.
Great space. Definately go back
Current photo exhibition/ contest is very interesting and some really high quality work.
Great space beautiful energy in the way the building flows on the inside walking you through a wonderland of photography, loved it
It's small venue, we liked the photos very much, you don't have to pay to enter they simply ask for donations.
Stunning place to visit. The gardens are fantastic and the rooms are wonderful. So many activities to take part in.
Such a nice place for chilling in summer. Beautiful gardens and good walk around the farm and the river  and eating at lentils. Love this place.

Love this place. We sometimes cycle here via bike track that follows merry creek and on a sunny Sunday spend some time around the period buildings followed by coffee and lentil as anything vegetarian meal!
Honest community hub. The farm is just next door. Amazing staff just hanging out to give you directions
I love this little cafe hidden away. You can visit the farm next door. Very lovely location and place.
Place has picked up. Service good. Food was fresh and good selection. You can have a glass of wine with lunch.
A big all-day breakfast menu as well as a good lunch menu. Everyone in my group was happy with their lunches. The rösti , fritters & pork burger were all good.
Nice bar and cafe. Great cheese selection.  Friendlt service.
One of my favourite cafes whenever I am in Richmond
Very good for a casual meal.
This is my favourite restaurant in Melbourne! The food is always, fresh, delicious and ever changing. The staff are friendly and the service is exceptional!

Just got ushered in by adoring fans seated outside. Stunning fusion dishes available of various cuisines and all done with such meticulous care! I was having multiple flavors hit me over the course of only my first mouthful of caulfiflower! Neatly put together interior and interesting looking retail products. Officially a fanboy after 1 meal.
Delicious food and friendly staff. Very reasonably priced
Love this place!  Amazing food, great selection and lovely staff!
Great vegetarian menu .very fresh and tasty.Good sized serves and reasonably priced
Great hot soup! Good portion! Great tea for a day to start.
Beef brisket was fresh and tasty. Ordered a large ($15) which was the perfect size for two. Service is OK, but you can only pay with cash.

I came in around 8.30pm, it wasn't very busy so staff had some down time and were sitting at the back resting. 

They greeted me to my seat and resumed back to their seats. One then proceeded to pop blackheads in the mirror!?!?.... Personally i wouldn't do it in public let alone whilst at work handling food!

Luckily she was not the one preparing or serving the food i ordered, which was average by the way.. 

Won't be coming back unless all other options are exhausted.

Forgot to mention it's cash only so come prepared!
Was introduced to Pho at this Restaurant, and still have yet to find one better, best pho in town

Pros: Food is alright but better than other stores within CBD, Good portions and price, quick service, mostly friendly waiters.
Cons: there's some weird smell coming from the back right corner of the store, don't think anyone would want to be seated there, and it's definitely not coming from the kitchen/food either. And one of the female waitresses is a bit rude and no eftpos too.

My friend has been there a few times and recommended it.  Well let me tell u, it was worth  the trip. I had Delicious corn fritters, avocado, chilli jam and also ordered a poached egg.  The 2 different toasted bread was devine as well. I have to say it was the best coffee ever..  my friend had the pancakes with ricotta and berries. Again delicious.  We finished up splitting an escargot pastry and another coffee. The incredible  assortment  of cakes and breads were amazing.. reasonable priced at about $25 each..
It a  small place with about 12 tables... its worth the wait..

I will be completely honest, it's extremely rare for me to ever make an effort to write a negative review about a company or business, but I truly believe this place was warranted. I came to Babka today eager to try a pie. I approach the counter & order a beef, red wine & mushroom pie. I was asked if I would like to take it away and agreed  - it was reasonably priced at $7.50. I sat down & waited for the pie to come out. The woman then approached me and asked if I was going to eat here, and I said actually I think so, I want to eat it really quickly, and make it to my meeting. She then told me if I wanted to eat here, then I would have to pay an extra $6.50 because they charge double to eat in. I laughed and asked are you serious? what is the logic behind that? She proceeded, that cafe is very small, with limited seats & serve bread and salad with it as well. I told them I don't want any bread or salad, and there are 30 open seats, I just want to eat my pie. I refused to pay the extra 6.50 and took the pie away. The pie seemed to have amazing potential if it wasn't COLD. Still amazed at how bad the service was here.
Best Danishes and baked products in Melbourne. I've been a loyal fan for over twenty years. Babka never changes and never compromises.

This place was my favourite as a little girl and I'd literally reminisced about their shoofly buns for 20 years before I went back to that side of town and had some recently. I had some doubts as to whether they'd be as good as the fruit buns of my dreams, but they absolutely were. They freeze well and I'll certainly be back for more (not too often as they are bad for my teeth however)!
Great food. Nice atmosphere. You can buy some bread and other bakery products as well

I definitely usually eat meat with most meals, however, Vegie Bar was absolutely great. The food was super tasty and filling. The place has a great vibe to it, it fills up very quickly for the dinner service so get in quick (not sure if they take bookings). We ordered a couple of mains (one was the satay sauce with veges) and the sweet potato fries. The food arrives pretty quickly too. Good service from staff, definitely recommend checking this place out!

Very tasty vegetarian food, generous servings vibrant ambiance in a busy, convenient part of Brunswick St Fitzroy. Trends to be busy almost all the time but not bad in mid afternoon after say, 2pm. The staff are polite and often friendly depending on stress levels. The meals are nevertheless quick to arrive. You will be required to sit where you're told as they won't seat 2 people on a 3 seat table. Ever. It can also get very noisy especially if they have the music up. Some people enjoy that. I don't. That said, I doubt there's a vegetarian in Melbourne who hasn't tried thus place. And worst case... There are LOTS of other eating places and bars literally paces away. You'll never go hungry in Brunswick St Fitzroy.
so yummy!!. I'm not vegetarian and really enjoyed the food. The service is great as well. Good for groups but is always busy. Consider booking and arriving on time.

Best place to go for anything vegan or vegetarian. They have great healthy meals to choose from, been there a few times through the years.

Last time we went we had the dhal meal and the nacho plate. And can’t forget the raw chocolate drink. 

Highly recommended for a healthy meal. Great staff and relaxing environment.

One of my favourite places to eat in Melbourne!
Fresh, delicious vegan/vegetarian food. 
The staff always greet you with a smile and are lovely.
Sriachia hollandaise is a revelation! Great soundtrack. Friendly, attentive staff. Fair prices. Would be improved by more vegan options and nicer toilets. Overall, a great place for brunch :)

Waited about 40 mins for food to arrive despite the menu being fairly simple.

Inside aesthetic nice, but full so we sat outside where it was plain and cold.

On paying bill I noted some nice specials on board inside which we weren't told about.

Thick shake was not at all thick--just a milkshake. Tasted alright. I liked the menu in general although nothing was especially remarkable. 

Food was nice.

I really do appreciate the service. The people were lovely. Unfortunately it took quite a while for our food to come, I had to ask if it was on its way after 40 minutes. Though the garlic pizza was nice the blue cheese burger had literally no blue cheese on it (please correct me if I'm wrong, but I expected blue cheese?), it was Swiss cheese. Thanks for splitting the bill though.
Nice place, issues with parking.
Very nice food and staff members 😊😊😊

An absolute Aladin's Cave for anyone interested in food. Tim has curated a peerless collection of modern top sellers and older classics. All major cuisines represented and some surprising niches. This is a confluence of deep passion and know how. Come here to browse, find and seek advice.
Probably the best cookbook shop I've been to and best in Aust. Booksellers v. Informative and friendly. Nothing too much trouble.

Amazing little shop with all kinds of books around the topics of cooking, baking, food and drinks; from all areas of the world, and with a selection that goes from vintage rare-to-find (maybe nostalgic to some) to modern day. The location next to the market makes it ideal to check it out while shopping or visiting the market.
Awesome book place has most cooking books for other countries and traditional meals ect also curing meat
Great selection of books. Perfect for food and book lovers. The staff is very helpful.

The Jewel in Melbourne's crown is the Royal Exhibition Building.

Playing host to the 2019 flower and Garden show, this historical gem highlights what makes Melbourne so special. A short walk from Parliament station and accessible by tram, it serves as a welcome vista for patients of St Vincent's hospital.

We are so lucky to have preserved this building. I recommend everyone coming to Melbourne get acquainted with the building that started Australian Democracy.

It's worth noting that some restoration work is in progress at this time, but doesn't detract from visiting.

When the, now famous/infamous "Jeff's Shed" adjacent to the Crown Casino was built (Melbourne Exhibition Centre) on South Bank, it was to replace this beautiful old gem.It is still used for smaller exhibitions and is still the centre-piece of the annual Melbourne International Flower and Garden Show.Just use a beautiful day when you are free to wander at your leisure and take in the wonderful and shady gardens surrounding this magnificent example of old Melbourne architecture.Stroll past the lakes filled with ducks, geese and swans, and take your time to see the fine detail of this gorgeous domed structure for yourself. Inside is just as beautiful if there is some form of show/exhibit on at the time you are there.Failing that, take an impromptu picnic with you and sit on the lawns and just soak up the views and the sun.

We visited the Royal Exhibition building for the Melbourne flower show. The building is so beautiful inside and out, with so much history to it. I would recommend a visit here, especially if visiting the Melbourne Museum which is right next door!

There is underground parking just under the museum, which is a bit pricey but it is in a good location and saves time. There are also the surrounding gardens to enjoy.

Located in Carlton Gardens, the Royal Exhibition Building is one of the oldest exhibition pavilions remaining in the world!

One of my favourite sites and one of the most beautiful buildings in Melbourne, the Royal Exhibition Building is a place to put on your bucket list!

Housing a wide range of events for Fashion, Food and Art, the Royal Exhibition Building is quite breathtaking from the inside as well.

Royal Exhibition Building is very important to me and my history. The place itself is very immaculately clean and the architecture is just stunning. I really really recommend attending this place if there are any events on, even if you don't enjoy what's on, just to see the immense scope of the building and the beautiful interior and paintings. A very nice place, everyone has to visit here.

The Grainger Museum located at Melbourne University is a hidden gem. Stumbled upon while taking a Melbourne University walking tour. Percy Grainger was a true Aussie eccentric, genius of music composition and performance. In later life he proposed this museum to Melbourne University and supervised it's creation providing a unique range of memorabilia from his own collection. Well worth a visit.

A collection of exhibits illustrating the life of Australian-American composer, Percy Grainger. This Museum was established while Grainger was still alive and it's architecture and collection reflect the choices of Grainger himself.

Great arrangement of all items in he museum. They are all interesting and full of information. I must say whatever I saw in this museum was very unique  and all related to development of music in Australia. The staffs were very kind and ready to provide you information. Will definitely return for the next exhibition.

Cool museum hidden near Melbourne Uni Music Department. I went to see the Synthesizer exhibition in 2018, and that was epic. The staff are knowledgeable and passionate. A lovely little space with some awesome free exhibitions. Worth a look-see :)
Very qwirky - definitely worth a visit.
Great venue for small intimate shows. They've got a small bar at the front with reasonable prices. Be warned, only one toilet though.
Perfect setting for a mystical theatre performance. My friend and I saw Adam Yees adaptation of Carmilla - absolutely stunning. A beautiful performance!
Went to see the play Tonight! Very impressed, shocking and extremely funny with wonderful  actors..... loved it😂
Have loved going to see plays at La Mama theatre over the years. With the lack of funding to the arts in this country, La Mama is a very special place that enables people to practice their craft.
Amazing venue with great shows. Very helpful front of house. Drinks available including free tea and coffee.
If you planning to go to the zoo. This is your station. There is 5hr parking nearby for zoo visitor. It is only 5 minutes walk so very convenience.
Another nice, old style station. Close to the zoo, and a golf course. No toilets unfortunately, but accessible.

By far the best station on the Upfield line. Not only does it deliver you to the door of the esteemed Melbourne Zoo, but the journey through Royal Park itself (which I happen to have reviewed favourably in the past due to parties I'm told occur there) is a blissful, tree-filled escape from the droll brown/grey fencing that dominates so much of the train-enthusiasts experience of Melbourne's public transport infrastructure.
Another of Melbourne's beaut old stations - convenient to Melbourne zoo, too.
Small and cute trian station on Upfield line just next to 58 tram stop in Royal Park area.

Amazing place. Lots of tourist and locals comes to this place for the array of desserts and good coffee. Best place to hangout with your friends and family. Jam packed with people but still a nice place to hangout. Great desserts, perfectly designed cakes.

A very nice cafe/restaurants in the middle of the city. This eatery is huge, spacious, plenty of seats, clean, and well decorated.

Cake selections are plenty, the coffee is not bad as well as the service. It is so crowded even on the weekdays, prepare for a long line on the weekend I suppose.

Coffee is okay. Cakes and pastry are palatable. The savoury menu is just fine. The place is a bit loud. Service can be a bit slow, with some staff being great and others are in their own daydream. But it's one of the only late night cafes in the CBD and for that it get three stars.

Amazing Italian cafe brand that originated from and has a long history in Melbourne. You can experience a great variety of Italian cuisine including cakes, coffee, pizzas, pastas and more. The place is massive and worth a look around.
The coffee here is the best ive ever had! The cafe looks amazing with a variety of delicious desserts as well. Love coming here. The iced latte is amazing!

Great location and ambiance for friends to hang out and catch up. Really great coffee and plenty of things to try from. I love the great chocolate selections they have. The staff are polite and courteous. I like to try things out and most of the time, I love it. I am glad I was able to go there almost every week. It is a little bit fancy place, but totally worth everything.

Always a Lovley visit. The staff are nice and are always very happy to help if needed. The chocolate, what can I say? Is to die for! The coffee is good and the platters of tasters are a must have! Good for all ages as they have something for everyone. I would definitely recommend for someone who has a sweet tooth (or not) thank you!

Loved the coffee, loved the vibe! A brilliant place to hang out. Also, the hot chocolate is awesome and the selection of desserts here is pretty cool. The only thing that stops me from going here every week is the price - a little too fancy but it’s worth it!

Love this place! Am a regular. The chocolates are amazing and so are the dessert offerings. Recently tried the crumpets and the quality of the butter and jam made a simple tea something to remember. 
Some staff are more courteous than others making customer service slightly inconsistent between visits, but overall excellent!
Solid dessert chain. Pretty much what you'd expect. Decent chocolate and a reasonable price. Nothing too stand out about it.
Great place though a little small. Mainly pizza on menu. The secret is get the dessert pizza.
Grrat food, great service, great place for all kinds of occasions and kid friendly. Very clean and just a lovely experience overall. I love the chocolate pizzas mmmmm thanks
Amazing pizza and service. One of the best pizza houses in Melbourne. If you're into pizza, it's worth travelling for.
Old school neighbourhood pizza joint - delicious, authentic pizza and wine served the same - in tumblers. Loved it!
Fantastic Napoli Style Pizza with warm and friendly staff.

Amazing place. Lots of tourist and locals comes to this place for the array of desserts and good coffee. Best place to hangout with your friends and family. Jam packed with people but still a nice place to hangout. Great desserts, perfectly designed cakes.

A very nice cafe/restaurants in the middle of the city. This eatery is huge, spacious, plenty of seats, clean, and well decorated.

Cake selections are plenty, the coffee is not bad as well as the service. It is so crowded even on the weekdays, prepare for a long line on the weekend I suppose.

Coffee is okay. Cakes and pastry are palatable. The savoury menu is just fine. The place is a bit loud. Service can be a bit slow, with some staff being great and others are in their own daydream. But it's one of the only late night cafes in the CBD and for that it get three stars.

Amazing Italian cafe brand that originated from and has a long history in Melbourne. You can experience a great variety of Italian cuisine including cakes, coffee, pizzas, pastas and more. The place is massive and worth a look around.
The coffee here is the best ive ever had! The cafe looks amazing with a variety of delicious desserts as well. Love coming here. The iced latte is amazing!
When were there in 2016 when we took the freedom Cruise you are not able to go in but enjoy the breeze in the back. We also did a true of the orphanage which part of proceeds went to it.
It was lit! We enjoyed it!
Great locality for an outdoor wedding.
Under renovation but should become one of downtown's best place to visit starting in 2018.
Good
Lots of vegetarian options. Fried tofu with chili and lemongrass was awesome! Good veggie burger (soft patty) and crispy fries. Veggie noodle soup was okay. Very friendly staff and owner.
This restaurant in my option is the best one in Hoi An the food is first class,and is spotlessly clean cannot fault it at all,just had an amazing meal there will be back there tomorrow night
Most enjoyable evening in this lovely restaurant.. great food happy attentive staff and all proceeds go to humanitarian aid in indochina ..

We did the cooking tour as a group of 7 and had a really good time! We chose three dishes from a set menu, then went to the market to collect our fresh ingredients. The food was really nice and the staff were great! And all the proceeds go to a charitable organisation which is really cool.

Good cooking class, trip through the market to buy ingredients was fun, nice to have a guide to answer questions. Didn't get to make individual meals, shared use of one two burner stove but the food tasted good at the end.
